        "text": "I still haven’t read the paper but one aspect of the episode I found interesting was that having simpler software avoids bugs. It seems like this is being conflated with the idea of sacrificing efficiency for robustness. Where sometimes the simpler code\/algorithm is in fact less robust and the more robust implementation requires more code (and potentially more bugs).",
