    {
        "user": "U04Q53X6P7W",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1709702334.819469",
        "client_msg_id": "DAF8D64C-C294-4558-91F7-FAAE706A3081",
        "text": "I’d be interested in trying to disentangle the robustness from the simplicity dimensions when making tradeoffs. So finding new ways to structure software to be inherently more robust to bugs seems compelling yet difficult.\n\nOverall the contention between correctness, efficiency, and robustness seems to arise from the viewpoint that correctness is a binary proposition rather than a probabilistic measurement of the values we want our software to achieve. If we have a myopic view of correctness we’re leaving all the tradeoffs off the table.",
